{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17626077","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17626077"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:33:12+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:33:12+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17055"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17055","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17055"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.36,0.5,0,0,0.14]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9745"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77012"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9745","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9745"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17055"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62518"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5252"},{"type":"tags","id":"5253"},{"type":"tags","id":"5289"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22923"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23100"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77012","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/77012"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ECD20 is a surface protein expressed during specific stages of B lymphocyte development. Anti-CD20 monoclonal antibodies are commonly used in autoimmune conditions and lymphomas.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the effect of anti-CD20 monoclonal antibodies on B lymphocyte populations?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Depletes pre-B cells and early plasma cells","Depletes mature B cells while sparing stem and plasma cells","Depletes memory B cells and late plasma cells","Depletes stem cells and transitional B cells","Depletes plasma cells and germinal B cells"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDepletes mature B cells while sparing stem and plasma cells\u003C/strong\u003E is correct because CD20 expression begins at the pre-B cell stage and continues through mature and memory B cells, while being absent on early stem cells and terminally differentiated plasma cells.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDepletes pre-B cells and early plasma cells\u003C/strong\u003E - While pre-B cells express CD20, plasma cells do not express CD20 at any stage\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDepletes memory B cells and late plasma cells\u003C/strong\u003E - Plasma cells do not express CD20, though memory B cells are indeed affected\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDepletes stem cells and transitional B cells\u003C/strong\u003E - Stem cells do not express CD20 and are therefore unaffected\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDepletes plasma cells and germinal B cells\u003C/strong\u003E - Plasma cells do not express CD20 and are therefore not affected by anti-CD20 therapy\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis selective targeting makes anti-CD20 antibodies useful in treating conditions like rheumatoid arthritis and B cell lymphomas, while preserving the ability to generate new B cells from stem cells and maintaining some antibody production from existing plasma cells.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Monoclonal antibodies targeting CD20 deplete B cells while sparing stem cells and plasma cells.","Anti-CD20 antibodies are used to treat autoimmune conditions and B cell lymphomas.","CD20 is expressed on B cells from the pre-B cell stage through memory B cells, but not on plasma cells."],"references":["Casan JML, Wong J, Northcott MJ, Opat S. Anti-CD20 monoclonal antibodies: reviewing a revolution. Hum Vaccin Immunother. 2018;14(12):2820-2841. doi: 10.1080/21645515.2018.1508624. Epub 2018 Sep 6. PMID: 30096012; PMCID: PMC6343614.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62518"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17055"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62518","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62518"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-05T22:19:27+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-05T22:21:09+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9745"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77012"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":nu